<TITLE> Don't give up, Hasina urges people in handwritten letter </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com) - Sheikh Hasina has accused the government of framing false charges against her. In a letter addressed to the nation, she has urged people "not to give up and continue the movement to restore people's right". >>Hasina's handwritten letter bdnews24.com has obtained a copy of the handwritten letter that Hasina has jotted down apparently minutes before getting arrested Monday morning from her Dhanmondi home in Dhaka. Her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad has confirmed her handwriting. "She left it on her table," an extremely upset Azad told bdnews24.com Monday evening. In her letter that is visibly scribed in haste Hasina said, "The government is arresting me. I don't know where they are taking me." Claiming to have never done anything wrong, the former prime minister said, "Yet false charges have been framed (against me)." She expressed confidence in people and sought divine intervention as well. She has urged her comrades not to give up. "Resist the unjust from respective position. Do not compromise. The truth shall prevail." The Awami League chief expressed her will of being with the people "until death". She concluded the letter with "Joy Bangla" and "Joy Bangabandhu". bdnews24.com/sm
